summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from the Weyerhaeuser Timber Company, a corporation duly incorporated under the laws of the State of Washington, to The City of Seattle, dated the 18th day of September, in the year of our Lord nineteen hundred and eleven, to certain tracts of land situated in Sections one (1), three (3), four (4), and then (10), in Township twenty-one (21) North, Range Eight (8) East, W. M.; Sections three (3), four (4), five (5), nine (9), ten (10), eleven (11), fifteen (15), seventeen (17), twenty-three (23) and twenty-five (25) in Township Twenty-two (22) North, Range Eight (8) East, W. M.; and Section Thirty-one (31), Township Twenty-three (23) North, Range Eight (8) East, W. M., in King County, State of Washington, and appropriating Three Thousand Seven Hundred Fifty and 00/100 ($3750.00) Dollars in payment therefor from the Cedar River Water Shed Condemnation Fund.
